	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=164168><span id=Scholar>Derrict</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>627 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.12]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>ironic how I usually post something about DKP system and how the person who has the most points and places a bid on the item gets it.. then people reply with flames and such, hence the low score rating on my post LOL.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's just not worth posting anything on these items because it's always about what class should get ABC item.  95% of the people bickering here will never see these items and probably think it's being distributed with /random 0 1000.<br><br>There are numerous ways to distribute loot and the most fair way tends to be the DKP system for the high end raiding guilds.  The person that attends the raids gets rewardes with points and those points are used to bid on items.  When you win an item, points are reduced.   Pros: people that raid consistently with good attendance will have more than those who raid less, thus, they should be rewarded.  Also, each person can equip themself more efficiently because they aren't going to be as willing to waste points on an item that might not be much of an upgrade.  Cons: items will rot/destroyed when no one bids.  There's no point in bidding on an item that isn't much of an upgrade to you.  Once your guild farms a certain zone for awhile, most people either have the item already or have something better.  Usually by then the guild will move on to other zones that are more difficult.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>[65 Deceiver]<a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362635 target=akztarg> Derrict </a>(Halfling) &lt;<a href=HTTP://www.hossguild.org target=akztarg>Hoss</a>&gt;</td></tr>
